  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Merlot and Cabernet Sauvignon?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Merlot is generally softer and more approachable than Cabernet Sauvignon, with lower tannins and higher natural acidity. While Cabernet Sauvignon offers bold blackcurrant and cedar notes with firm structure, Merlot presents plush plum and chocolate flavors with silky tannins. Merlot also ripens earlier and thrives in cooler clay soils, whereas Cabernet Sauvignon prefers well-draining gravelly soils and warmer climates.</p>
