    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What are the biggest mistakes people make when buying Merlot?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">The most common mistake is choosing mass-produced, inexpensive Merlots that lack concentration and character, perpetuating negative stereotypes about the grape. Many buyers also overlook excellent Merlot-based blends from Bordeaux, focusing only on varietal bottlings and missing outstanding Right Bank wines. Another error is serving Merlot too warm, which masks its elegant fruit profile and makes the wine taste flat and alcoholic.</p>
